    "description": "Titanic and the Lifeboat Regulation Gap is a Cascade Effects episode about how small signals become system consequences.\n\nTitanic carried enough lifeboats to satisfy the law, but the law was measuring an older class of risk.\n\nRuntime: about 13 minutes.\n\nCascade Effects traces failures through mechanism, incentives, and institutional blind spots.\n\nChapters:\n0:00 Legal Answer, Wrong Question\n1:07 The Highest Bracket Failed To Scale\n2:02 Old Rules, New Ship\n3:37 Compliance Became Sufficient\n5:19 The Davits Knew More\n7:29 Capacity Became People\n8:36 The Rule Was Out Of Date\n10:21 People, Not Tonnage\n\n#CascadeEffects",
